<iframe id="gameFrame" src="your-game.html" frameborder="0"></iframe>

<style>
  html, body {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  
  #gameFrame {
    width: 100vw;
    height: 100vh;
   

To make the game fit the entire available space in its container (such as an `<iframe>` or the full browser window), you need to adjust the styles of the `#game` container and the outer `<div>`.  

### **Updated Code:**
This version ensures that the game stretches to fit the full viewport or its parent container.

```html
<div id="gameContainer">
    <div id="game"></div>
</div>

<style>
  html, body {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  #gameContainer {
    width: 100vw;
    height: 100vh;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
  }

  #game {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
  }
</style>

<script type="text/javascript">
    EJS_player = "#game";
    EJS_core = "gba";  
    EJS_gameUrl = "mkss.gba";
    EJS_pathtodata = "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/ethanaobrien/emulatorjs@main/data/";
</script>
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/ethanaobrien/emulatorjs@main/data/loader.js"></script>
